snippet.title: Medusa or a mermaid found dead

localized.description:
In Greek mythology, Medusa was a female monster or Gorgon described as having the face of a hideous human female with living venomous snakes in place of hair. She is also known for turning someone into a stone by directly gazing into her eyes.
The photos appeared to be as a female with snakes as her hair. She also seemed to look like a mermaid.

However, Facebook viewers got curious about these pictures and made a research. One viewer commented that it is a mermaid. Another commented, the photo is fake and it is a wax figure of a character from the movie Pirates of the Caribbean on Stranger Tides.



Whether the real life  Medusa or a mermaid, real or fake, there was no further details on when and where these photos were taken.

Moreover, according to scientists, 95% of our ocean is still unexplored. So we’ll never know, few years from now, we could prove that mermaid really exist or there are new creatures to be discovered.
